---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="About | ToyWebCreations"
  description="Why ToyWebCreations exists and what kind of web experiments it collects."
>
  <section class="copy-panel">
    <p class="copy-panel__eyebrow">About the site</p>
    <h1>ToyWebCreations is a portfolio of small interactive projects.</h1>
    <p>
      The goal is to keep focused interactive ideas in one place: logic puzzles, small simulations,
      generators, and other browser-native projects that are better experienced directly than described at length.
    </p>
    <p>
      Each project gets two things: a playable page and a short writeup. The demo should be obvious
      immediately. The writeup should make the idea legible to someone new, while still leaving enough
      implementation detail for another developer to follow the thread.
    </p>
    <p>
      The site has a consistent retro-inspired visual style, but the content is meant to stay clear and direct.
    </p>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
